reviewText:
Orhto Bug B Gon Insect Killer for Lawns and Gardens kills 235 listed insects.

It can be used on:
roses, flowers, shrubs & small trees;
around house foundations, porches, patios and stored lumber (but not firewood);
lawns;
home vegetable gardens, melons & fruit and nut trees

The label says tomatoes can be sprayed one day before harvest;  corn, peas, Lima beans, etc three days before harvest.  I don't adhere to organic methods, but this seems risky to me.  The label says it is safe for people and pets as soon as it has dried.

I noticed Ortho is now owned by Scott's... as is Miracle Grow.
